sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Coding sequence for a green fluorescence protein back translated for homo sapiens
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a coding sequence for a green fluorescence protein produced by the aequorea victoria jellyfish. The sequence has been back translated for use in homo sapiens.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Michael Sieverts
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The source of this part is the aequorea victoria jellyfish.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is designed for use in eukaryotic cells, so the amino acid sequence was back translated for use in homo sapiens.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: CCBD
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequence codes for the central cell binding domain (CCBD) consisting of human Fibronectin Type III Modules 8-10.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Farhad Farjood
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The amino acid sequence is back-translated to DNA sequence which is codon-optimized for Homo sapiens
